Google Cloud Storage is a scalable object storage service designed to store and manage large amounts of unstructured data such as images, videos, audio files, documents, and backups.
Benefits of Google Cloud Storage
•	Highly Scalable: Can store massive amounts of data without capacity limitations. 
•	Durability and Reliability: Provides secure and reliable data storage. 
•	Cost-Effective: Pay only for the storage used. 
•	Easy Accessibility: Data can be accessed from anywhere through the internet. 
•	Security: Supports encryption and access control mechanisms. 
Example
A video streaming company can store thousands of movies and video files in Google Cloud Storage and deliver them to users worldwide efficiently.
10. A system administrator wants to manage Microsoft Azure resources directly from a web browser without installing additional software. Which Azure feature can be used and why?
The system administrator should use Azure Cloud Shell.
Why Azure Cloud Shell?
Azure Cloud Shell is a browser-based command-line interface provided by Microsoft Azure that allows users to manage Azure resources directly from a web browser without installing any software locally.
Benefits of Azure Cloud Shell
•	No Installation Required: Accessible directly through the Azure Portal. 
•	Browser-Based Access: Can be used from any device with an internet connection. 
•	Supports Bash and PowerShell: Users can choose their preferred command-line environment. 
•	Azure Resource Management: Enables creation, configuration, and monitoring of Azure resources. 
•	Built-in Tools: Includes Azure CLI, PowerShell, and scripting support. 
Example
A system administrator can log in to the Azure Portal, open Azure Cloud Shell, and create or manage virtual machines, storage accounts, and networks directly from the browser.

